<subSubSection id="C3036541FFD48B0D5E8FFD1A20EBFC0D" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFD48B0D5E8FFD1A22A8FD0A" blockId="39.[189,457,648,674]" box="[189,457,648,674]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<heading id="D0EE81A6FFD48B0D5E8FFD1A22A8FD0A" bold="true" box="[189,457,648,674]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5E8FFD1A22A8FD0A" bold="true" box="[189,457,648,674]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFD48B0D5E8FFD2520EBFC0D" blockId="39.[188,1399,695,933]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD48B0D5E8FFD2522CCFD79" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,429,695,721]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsonga" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5E8FFD2522CCFD79" box="[189,429,695,721]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Ebenacobius tsonga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFD48B0D5F8AFD2A2113FD7A" box="[440,626,696,722]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished by the following combination of features: simple claws, prothorax and elytra similarly pale brown, with two longitudinal dark bands on prothorax not reaching apical margin and elytra with a row of recumbent and subcontiguous setae on interstriae 5–10 of elytra. This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD48B0D5CC0FCB02027FC93" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[754,838,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pedi" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5CC0FCB02065FC93" box="[754,772,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5D21FCB32027FC93" box="[787,838,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">pedi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFD48B0D5D7FFCB3209CFC93" box="[845,1021,801,827]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD48B0D5A04FCB02640FC93" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[1078,1313,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippopotamorum" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5A04FCB02640FC93" box="[1078,1313,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">E. hippopotamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFD48B0D5B1AFCB32277FCF7" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but in both species setae on elytra are minute, not forming a row of subcontiguous setae laterally. The body of penis in 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD48B0D5F85FCF521C5FC29" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[439,676,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsonga">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5F85FCF521C5FC29" box="[439,676,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Ebenacobius tsonga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also much shorter (W:L ratio: 0.5; 
<figureCitation id="13222A4FFFD48B0D5A6EFCF527DDFC2A" box="[1116,1212,871,898]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[351,1247,266,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-11@33.[339,1248,265,1815]" captionText="Fig. 6 (part 1). A–I. Male genitalia of Ebenacobius Haran gen. nov., penis in dorsal (left) and lateral (right) view.A. E. curvisetis Haran gen. et sp. nov.B. E. rectirostrisHaran gen. et sp. nov.C. E. duplicatus Haran gen. et sp. nov. D. E. grobbelaarae Haran gen. et sp. nov. E. E. costalis (Fåhraeus, 1844) gen. et comb. nov. F. E. thoracicus Haran gen. et sp. nov. G. E. xhosa Haran gen. et sp. nov. H. E. san Haran gen. et sp. nov. I. E. kuscheli Haran gen. et sp. nov. A–I = not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536655/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 6M</figureCitation>
) than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD48B0D5B11FCFA2616FC29" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[1315,1399,871,898]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pedi">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5B11FCFA2654FC29" box="[1315,1333,872,897]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5B76FCF52616FC29" box="[1348,1399,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">pedi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD48B0D5EDDFC1922B8FC0C" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[239,473,906,932]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippopotamorum">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5EDDFC1922B8FC0C" box="[239,473,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">E. hippopotamorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(W:L ratio at least 0.40; 
<figureCitation id="13222A4FFFD48B0D5CCDFC18201CFC0D" box="[767,893,906,933]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[351,1247,266,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-11@33.[339,1248,265,1815]" captionText="Fig. 6 (part 1). A–I. Male genitalia of Ebenacobius Haran gen. nov., penis in dorsal (left) and lateral (right) view.A. E. curvisetis Haran gen. et sp. nov.B. E. rectirostrisHaran gen. et sp. nov.C. E. duplicatus Haran gen. et sp. nov. D. E. grobbelaarae Haran gen. et sp. nov. E. E. costalis (Fåhraeus, 1844) gen. et comb. nov. F. E. thoracicus Haran gen. et sp. nov. G. E. xhosa Haran gen. et sp. nov. H. E. san Haran gen. et sp. nov. I. E. kuscheli Haran gen. et sp. nov. A–I = not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6536655" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6536655/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 6L, N</figureCitation>
).
