<subSubSection id="C3036541FFD48B0D5E8FFC5E2612FBF3" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFD48B0D5E8FFC5E2225FC4E" blockId="39.[189,324,972,998]" box="[189,324,972,998]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<heading id="D0EE81A6FFD48B0D5E8FFC5E2225FC4E" bold="true" box="[189,324,972,998]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5E8FFC5E2225FC4E" bold="true" box="[189,324,972,998]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFD48B0D5E8FFC682612FBF3" blockId="39.[189,1400,1018,1115]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
This species name is dedicated to the Tsonga people, inhabitants of the north-eastern provinces of the 
<collectingCountry id="F30E765AFFD48B0D5E8CFB8F228CFB9F" box="[190,493,1053,1079]" name="South Africa" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Republic of South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49DDF828FFD48B0D5FCDFB8F210CFB9F" box="[511,621,1053,1079]" country="South Africa" name="Limpopo" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Limpopo</collectingRegion>
and Mpumalalnga). These peoples share this land with the Pedi peoples, as do 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD48B0D5F58FBD022B9FBF3" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[362,472,1090,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsonga" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5F58FBD022B9FBF3" box="[362,472,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">E. tsonga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFD48B0D5FD2FBD321F1FBF3" box="[480,656,1089,1115]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFD48B0D5CFBFBD0207DFBF3" authority="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat, 2022" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" box="[713,796,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ebenacobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pedi" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFD48B0D5CFBFBD0207DFBF3" box="[713,796,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">E. pedi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25E57A3FFD48B0D5D11FBD320B2FBF3" box="[803,979,1089,1115]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, apparently on the same host plant.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
